{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":"Miguel de Guzman","homeCity":"Philippines"}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cfd4acf19dc7e240a67b4d3c9350081e/d1d06/silverback1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 125.67049808429118%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"silverback\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/cfd4acf19dc7e240a67b4d3c9350081e/c739e/silverback1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cfd4acf19dc7e240a67b4d3c9350081e/8ee9c/silverback1.jpg 148w,\n/static/cfd4acf19dc7e240a67b4d3c9350081e/ebbe7/silverback1.jpg 295w,\n/static/cfd4acf19dc7e240a67b4d3c9350081e/c739e/silverback1.jpg 590w,\n/static/cfd4acf19dc7e240a67b4d3c9350081e/5413e/silverback1.jpg 885w,\n/static/cfd4acf19dc7e240a67b4d3c9350081e/d1d06/silverback1.jpg 1044w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3><b><em>Screaming Biology!</em></b></h3>\n<br/>\n<p><em>Been doing a lot of deep dive on human behavior biology and personality traits instead of focusing on my advanced javascript course - which I do not know if its a logical way of consuming content. I’m just so fascinated of the capabilities of our brain and how evolution worked for eons to create us and we clearly started from apes. The field of primatology paved way for a lot of scientists and researchers to study how pre-human nature works and gave us a better understanding of topics like infanticide, aggression, maternal instincts and sexual preferrences.</em> </p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/dc29f79ff0749ad072a29527307011ba/e6a35/robertsapolsky1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 110.26986506746626%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"robertsapolsky\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/dc29f79ff0749ad072a29527307011ba/c739e/robertsapolsky1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/dc29f79ff0749ad072a29527307011ba/8ee9c/robertsapolsky1.jpg 148w,\n/static/dc29f79ff0749ad072a29527307011ba/ebbe7/robertsapolsky1.jpg 295w,\n/static/dc29f79ff0749ad072a29527307011ba/c739e/robertsapolsky1.jpg 590w,\n/static/dc29f79ff0749ad072a29527307011ba/5413e/robertsapolsky1.jpg 885w,\n/static/dc29f79ff0749ad072a29527307011ba/4efde/robertsapolsky1.jpg 1180w,\n/static/dc29f79ff0749ad072a29527307011ba/e6a35/robertsapolsky1.jpg 1334w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><em>Dr. Robert Sapolsky’s book “Behave” is so fundamental in my understanding of filtering what is good and bad as we are wired of so much neural networks where it is rather becoming difficult to say that we are all making decisions as a cause of free will. A highly recommended book!</em></p>\n<p><em>He’s one of the most fascinating persons I’ve come across with in the field of biology especially primatology. He’s lecture on the topic is bloody on point as he explains how our so called human nature came to reality in great detail. I’m just on lecture 3 of 25 and I’m in awe of the depth of progress that we have accomplished in the field. I still need to turn them though to audiobooks so I can consume them while cycling and at work - whenever there will be downtime. Here is the link to <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLpXaCv0b7h12LpVunZ361VfCBQSwi_2e8\">the lecture series</a>.</em></p>\n<p><em>Training myself to understand more complex topics paved way to better conversations and enabled me as well to increase my empathy as our genetic code is not perfect. Even though natural selection is inaccurate at most, it developed certain conditions for our species to dominate in the present.</em></p>","excerpt":"Screaming Biology! Been doing a lot of deep dive on human behavior biology and personality traits instead of focusing on my advanced…","fields":{"tagSlugs":["/tags/creating-art/","/tags/biology/","/tags/psychology/","/tags/philosophy/","/tags/blog/"]},"frontmatter":{"title":"Primatology","tags":["creating-art","biology","psychology","philosophy","blog"],"date":"August 25, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/primatology/"}}